<h2>Solar Incentives in Phoenix</h2>
<p>Phoenix residents can take advantage of multiple solar incentives that significantly reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost, including equipment and installation, through 2032. This credit steps down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. Arizona offers additional state-level benefits, including a solar equipment sales tax exemption that saves homeowners hundreds of dollars on system purchases. The state also provides a property tax exemption, meaning the added home value from solar panels won't increase property taxes.</p>

