<p>When selecting a solar installer in Phoenix, prioritize companies with proper Arizona licensing, including the required electrical and solar contractor licenses. Look for installers with extensive local experience who understand Phoenix's unique challenges, such as extreme heat installation conditions, monsoon weather considerations, and APS interconnection requirements. Top solar companies should offer comprehensive warranties covering equipment (typically 20-25 years for panels, 10-25 years for inverters) and workmanship (minimum 10 years). Verify that installers carry proper insurance and bonding, and check their Better Business Bureau ratings and online reviews from local customers.</p>

